<item>
            <title>[SOLR-2139] Wrong cast from string to float</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2139</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Class java.org.apache.solr.spelling.suggest.Suggester str 60&lt;br/&gt;
Invalid cast from String to Float.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; threshold = config.get(THRESHOLD_TOKEN_FREQUENCY) == null ? 0.0f&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            : (Float) config.get(THRESHOLD_TOKEN_FREQUENCY);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;config.get returns String, We want just cast it to Float.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;correct code should be like &lt;br/&gt;
 threshold = config.get(THRESHOLD_TOKEN_FREQUENCY) == null ? 0.0f&lt;br/&gt;
            : Float.valueOf(config.get(THRESHOLD_TOKEN_FREQUENCY).trim()).floatValue();&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
